      "id": "j101-modes",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "## 💡 JShell Mode vs Java Mode\n\nThis notebook shows **both** approaches side-by-side.\n\n| | JShell Mode (default) | Java Mode (full program) |\n|---|---|---|\n| **What it is** | Interactive REPL — like Python | Full Java class with `main()` |\n| **When to use** | Quick experiments, exploring APIs | Production code, learning class structure |\n| **Class wrapper** | Not required | Required (`public class Foo { ... }`) |\n| **Run** | Each cell runs immediately | Write full class, then run |\n| **Cell label** | 🔵 **JShell** prefix in comments | ☕ **Java** prefix in comments |\n\n> Both work in Arima Notebooks! JShell cells run top-to-bottom sharing state. Java cells are self-contained.",
